ai_flow.client.ai_flow_client module¶

class ai_flow.client.ai_flow_client.AIFlowClient(server_uri='localhost:50051', notification_service_uri=None, project_config: Optional[ai_flow.project.project_config.ProjectConfig] = None)[source]¶

Bases: ai_flow.endpoint.client.metadata_client.MetadataClient, ai_flow.endpoint.client.model_center_client.ModelCenterClient, notification_service.client.NotificationClient, ai_flow.endpoint.client.metric_client.MetricClient, ai_flow.endpoint.client.scheduler_client.SchedulerClient

Client of an AIFlow Server that manages metadata store, model center and notification service.

The constructor of the NotificationClient.

Parameters

  • server_uri – Target server uri/uris. If enable_ha is True, multiple uris separated by “,” can be accepted.

  • default_namespace – The default namespace that this client is working on.

  • enable_ha – Enable high-available functionality.

  • list_member_interval_ms – When enable_ha is True, this client will request the living members periodically. A member means a server node of the Notification server cluster. This param specifies the interval of the listing member requests.

  • retry_interval_ms – When enable_ha is True and a rpc call has failed on all the living members, this client will retry until success or timeout. This param specifies the retry interval.

  • retry_timeout_ms – When enable_ha is True and a rpc call has failed on all the living members, this client will retry until success or timeout. This param specifies the retry timeout.

  • sender – The identify of the client.
